        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 7 at 3:48PM EDT until July 7 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Buffalo NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBUF

The National Weather Service in Buffalo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Allegany County in western New York...

* Until 445 PM EDT.

* At 348 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Wellsville,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Wellsville, Alfred, Whitesville, Scio, Andover, Belmont, Alma,
Almond, West Almond, and Stannards.

This includes Interstate 86 between exits 32 and 33.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
